!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %meta{'charset'=>'utf-8'}
    %title Line Length-icator
    %meta{'http-equiv'=>'X-UA-Compatible','content'=>'IE=edge,chrome=1'}
    %meta{'name'=>'viewport','content'=>'width=device-width'}
    %link{'rel'=>'stylesheet','href'=>'css/styles.css'}
    %link{'rel'=>'stylesheet','href'=>'http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/3.1.1/css/font-awesome.css'}
    %link{'href'=>'http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Merriweather:400,900,400italic,700|Merriweather+Sans:400,700','rel'=>'stylesheet','type'=>'text/css'}
  %body
    .container
      %h1
        Line Length-icator
        %small Your readabil-a-buddy!
      .content(contentEditable) I'm always trying to find the best line length for my paragraphs, headings, and other text. I built this to avoid manually counting characters (woof). Paste some text right in here! &#9786;
      .metrics
        %label{:for => "charMax"}
          Target Line Length:
          %input#charMax{:type => "text", :value => "66"}
          characters
        %label{:for => "fontSize"}
          Font Size:
          %input#fontSize{:type => "text", :value => "20"}
          px
        %label{:for => "cWidth"}
          Width:
          %input#cWidth{:type => "text"}(disabled)
          px
        %button#break Break Word
      %button.go
        %i.icon-magic
        Visualize
    %script{'src'=>'http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.10.0/jquery.min.js'}
    %script{'src'=>'http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery-resize/1.1/jquery.ba-resize.min.js'}
    %script{'src'=>'js/scripts.min.js'}